  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Permanent Residency Path</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The White Card is explicitly designed as a temporary solution—it does NOT lead to permanent residency or citizenship in Hungary. After 2 years (maximum), you must leave for at least 6 months before reapplying. If long-term EU settlement is your goal, consider Portugal, Spain, or Germany.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Planning to Bring Family</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Hungary's White Card doesn't allow family reunification. Spouses and children cannot join you on dependent visas (except children born in Hungary during permit validity). Each family member who wants to live in Hungary must independently qualify for their own White Card.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Inconsistent Income Documentation</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You need 6 months of bank statements showing consistent €3,000+/month income. Months significantly below the threshold raise questions. If your income varies, ensure your 6-month average clearly exceeds €3,000 and prepare explanations for any dips.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the €10,000 Savings Requirement</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Beyond monthly income, you must show €10,000 in your bank account. Some applicants focus only on income and forget this requirement. Ensure your balance shows at least €10,000 at the time of application.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the 30-Day White Card Deadline</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">After entering Hungary on your D visa, you have only 30 days to apply for the White Card. Don't get caught up exploring Budapest and miss this deadline. Schedule your immigration office appointment soon after arrival.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

